cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY. 

This paper is about testing whether standard deep learning methods can learn efficient representations posited by theories of deep representation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is focused on the development and analysis of algorithms that can learn from and make predictions on data. 

The paper also involves training deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which is focused on the study of artificial neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. 

The paper deals with learning functions, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which is focused on the development of intelligent agents that can perceive their environment and take actions to achieve goals. 

The paper also mentions the fast Fourier transform, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), which is focused on the development of algorithms for analyzing and understanding visual data. 

Finally, the paper involves understanding the limitations of deep networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control), which is focused on the analysis and design of complex systems.
